// G13: module private state persists across calls
// Before fix: every call reset module state to its initial value —
// a counter::increment() call did not change anything visible on next call.
// The write-back mechanism after each function execution fixes this.

<# ./g13_counter_mod <= c

// Three increments — count should reach 3
c::increment()
c::increment()
c::increment()
n = c::get_value()
>> n ¶

// Reset, count goes back to 0
c::reset()
n2 = c::get_value()
>> n2 ¶

// Increment then decrement
c::increment()
c::increment()
c::decrement()
n3 = c::get_value()
>> n3 ¶

// Private state is NOT accessible via dot (only through exported functions)
// c.count would be a runtime error — not tested here to avoid failing the suite
